   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1866_02_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>W. Brummer<lb/>AMSTERDAM - ROTTERDAM.<lb/>Messrs<lb/>L. Kniffler +Co.
                Yokohama<lb/>Amsterdam 9th ⟨Feb⟩ Jan 1866<lb/>Since my last letter from 25th Jan. I
                have received your <lb/>esteemed letter from 1st Dec., but the last mail brought no
                <lb/>letters from you; just a report from which I gather with<lb/>pleasure that the
                rate is finally rising again and <lb/>that taffachelas + shirtings are better now.
                _<lb/>We have received the remittance £1549. 9/7. for the calculation <lb/>of 20
                boxes of taffachelas from the consignment above._<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>The loss is: invoice</cell>
                  <cell>f 20,008. 55.</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>Net prov. excl. interest etc.</cell>
                  <cell>14,468. 03</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell/>
                  <cell>f 5540. 52</cell>
               </row>
            </table> Please kindly take note of this because I provided a <lb/>100% advance
                guaranteed by you (correspondence Gildemeister /<lb/>Schröder)._ While I harbour no
                worries at all that we are<lb/>going to suffer in this respect, I ask to have this
                noted as a <lb/>matter of form. _ You know that furthermore there is a <lb/>100%
                advance under your guarantee on<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>O;</cell>
                  <cell>200 kelden of jenever[?]</cell>
                  <cell>f 1372.20.</cell>
                  <cell> p Minister Wall<lb/>for<lb/>v.Baum</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>
                     <figure>
                        <figDesc>Company sign. On the right and left two circles connected by a rhombus, in the circles the letters V and D</figDesc>
                     </figure>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>3 4/7/2/5 11 boxes taffachelas</cell>
                  <cell>" 10868.25</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>W</cell>
                  <cell>½ 2 " manna</cell>
                  <cell>" 227.35.</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>B. C.</cell>
                  <cell>1/150[?] 150 " metal sheets</cell>
                  <cell>" 2472.75.</cell>
               </row>
            </table> Enclosed you will find the invoice extract for <lb/>1865 with a balance
                of[?]<lb/>f 10,966.26 per 1st Jan.[?] in my favour._<lb/>Additionally, the
                commissions Bohlen + Co at 1½ + 1%[?]<lb/>are outstanding with fl. 505.46.,
                thereafter the entire commission</p>
         <pb facs="1866_02_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>for 1865, which is due semi-annually; furthermore I reclaim<lb/>seriously but
                politely the restitution of <del rend="overstrike">the </del>
            <del rend="overstrike"> your</del>
            <lb/>whole half commission + bill of exchange[?] commission of<lb/> 3¾ % on the
                wares, which I have unfortunately got stuck<lb/>with and for which I have so far
                balanced the accounts for stearin <lb/>candles per “Antie” + taffachelas per “D. F.
                Visser” at a great loss and <lb/>if then, with all these troubles and losses, I
                further notice <lb/>an approx. £ 1,000_ cash advance[?] since almost a whole
                <lb/>year ago, my head really starts swimming. _<lb/>I followed[?] last year’s
                current account because it was<lb/>decided in the end that the entries as a whole
                <lb/>were to be made out to Yokohama._ The commission<lb/>note credits for 1864
                have, as you know, been accepted by Bollenh. <lb/>+ Co. and are by f40np[?] Europ[?]
                Bank, were not used in 18[?]64 --<lb/>in 1865. only £1,700. or f20,400 have been
                used._ The f 34.25_<lb/>postage by Bollenhagen+Co has been debited at their
                instruction[?]._<lb/>We received the Ch/Ch[?]from Nagasaki (some time ago, I wrote
                <lb/>to you (at the time) for you to understand that I cannot keep any <lb/>Ch/Ch in
                dollars as my invoices have to paid be in Guilders! <lb/>The balancing dollar
                invoice for sales I am disregarding. <lb/>Please kindly check the Ch/Ch and after
                their verification I will<lb/>promptly acquire remittances for the balance +
                for<lb/>the commissions incl. those for 1865._<lb/>The somewhat more favourable
                reports from there <lb/>still do not suffice yet to make further shipments and
                <lb/>nothing is being done here yet._</p>
         <pb facs="1866_02_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_W_Brummer_Amsterdam_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <p>Cotton has dropped in the last 14 days so that <lb/>last week one could buy
                midlupland for 18d, <lb/>a type that today is back at 19¼.__<lb/>Money somewhat more
                plentiful but discount in <lb/>London still 8%, also 6% to 7%___<lb/>Yours most
                respectfully <lb/>W. Brummer</p>
      </body>
   </text>
